      <p></p>
<p>Losing a friend is a devastating experience.  Offering sympathy and support to a friend dealing with grief requires genuine empathy and understanding. Your words can make a significant difference in their healing process.</p>
<li>I am so incredibly sorry for your loss.  Thinking of you.</li>
<li>I'll always remember [deceased's name]'s kindness and [positive quality].</li>
<li>My heart breaks for you during this difficult time.</li>
<li>Please let me know if there's anything I can do to help.</li>
<li>I'm here for you, no matter what you need.</li>
<li>My thoughts and prayers are with you.</li>
<li>You and your family are in my thoughts.</li>
<li>Sending you love and support.</li>
<li>[deceased's name] will be dearly missed.</li>
<li>May your memories bring you comfort.</li>
<li>I'm deeply saddened by the loss of your friend.</li>
<li>I'm thinking of you and sending all my love.</li>
<li>I'll always cherish our memories of [deceased's name].</li>
